<subSubSection id="C3213283FFACF928FF5BF98BFAC7F890" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B846108FFACF928FF5BF98BFAC7F890" blockId="62.[151,1436,1488,1854]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFACF928FF5BF98BFE8BF9F5" bold="true" box="[196,273,1601,1627]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">Notes.</emphasis>
This is another large species (7.0–8.5 mm) with a W-Mediterranean distribution, the presence of which in Sardinia, repeatedly reported in the literature (see above), was not confirmed by the study of the several collections. However, recently it was recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F32C2198FFACF928FC1FF947FC43F909" box="[896,985,1677,1703]" name="France" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">Corsica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA1CF9FFACF928FC71F947FBEEF909" author="Secq, M." box="[1006,1140,1677,1703]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" pagination="45 - 46" refId="ref76085" refString="Secq, M. (1998) Quelques nouveautes sur les Histerides de la faune de France (Col.). L'Entomologiste, 54 (1), 45 - 46." type="journal article" year="1998">Secq 1998</bibRefCitation>
); this, together with the records from mainland 
<collectingCountry id="F32C2198FFACF928FE32F979FE79F963" box="[429,483,1715,1741]" name="Italy" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">Italy</collectingCountry>
cited by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA1CF9FFACF928FDCDF979FCE0F963" author="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P." box="[594,890,1715,1741]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" pagination="173 - 175" refId="ref75329" refString="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P. (2005) Insecta Coleoptera Histeridae. In: Ruffo, S. &amp; Stoch, F. (Eds), Checklist e distribuzione della fauna italiana. Memorie del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 2. serie, Sezione Scienze della Vita, 16, pp. 173 - 175, with data on CD-ROM." type="journal article" year="2005">Penati and Vienna (2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA1CF9FFACF928FC17F979FC4EF963" author="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P." box="[904,980,1715,1741]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" pagination="173 - 175" refId="ref75399" refString="Penati, F. &amp; Vienna, P. (2006 a) Insecta Coleoptera Histeridae. In: Ruffo, S. &amp; Stoch, F. (Eds), Checklist and distribution of the Italian fauna. Memorie del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Verona, 2. serie, Sezione Scienze della Vita, 17, pp. 173 - 175, with data on CD-ROM." type="journal article" year="2006">2006a</bibRefCitation>
), allows us to suppose that the species could actually occur in 
<collectingRegion id="49FFAFEAFFACF928FE32F913FD95F95D" box="[429,527,1753,1779]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
but was not found for many decades due to its rarity (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA1CF9FFACF928FB0EF913FAA5F95D" author="Yelamos, T." box="[1169,1343,1753,1779]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" refId="ref77185" refString="Yelamos, T. (2002) Coleoptera, Histeridae. In: Ramos, M. A. et al. (Eds), Fauna Iberica, vol. 17. Museo nacional de Ciencias naturales, CSIC, Madrid, 411 pp." type="book" year="2002">Yélamos 2002</bibRefCitation>
) or that some specimens may be hidden in the collections, confused with melanic specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B1A8BFFACF928FACCF935FEC4F890" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Hister" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrimaculatus">
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFACF928FACCF935FEC4F890" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">Hister quadrimaculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="B94FBD1AFFACF928FEF1F8EFFE16F890" box="[366,396,1829,1854]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">cf.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA1CF9FFACF928FE0DF8EEFD8BF890" author="Secq, M." box="[402,529,1828,1854]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" pagination="45 - 46" refId="ref76085" refString="Secq, M. (1998) Quelques nouveautes sur les Histerides de la faune de France (Col.). L'Entomologiste, 54 (1), 45 - 46." type="journal article" year="1998">Secq 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA1CF9FFACF928FD83F8EEFD51F890" author="Yelamos, T." box="[540,715,1828,1854]" pageId="62" pageNumber="259" refId="ref77185" refString="Yelamos, T. (2002) Coleoptera, Histeridae. In: Ramos, M. A. et al. (Eds), Fauna Iberica, vol. 17. Museo nacional de Ciencias naturales, CSIC, Madrid, 411 pp." type="book" year="2002">Yélamos 2002</bibRefCitation>
). In any case, its presence in 
<collectingRegion id="49FFAFEAFFACF928FBBFF8EEFB18F890" box="[1056,1154,1828,1854]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="62" pageNumber="259">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
needs confirming.
</paragraph>
